  questions:
  - question: 'In front of you is a red button. If you press it, the bully that made
      your life hell for years will die suddenly. And no one will ever know that
      you did it. '
    answer1: I press the button to get my revenge
    answer2: "I don\u2019t touch it, I\u2019m no killer "
  - question: 'You are walking by a construction site. Looking up you see a menacing
      metal beam about to fall on a group of construction workers.   You have a chance
      of saving them if you push them out of the way but that puts you right on the
      spot to be crushed to death by said beam. Is it worth jumping in ? '
    answer1: 'I stay put and let the gruesome scene unfold '
    answer2: "I jump in the way to push the group out of harm\u2019s way, aware of
      the consequences "
  - question: "You and your loved one got arrested and are being interrogated apart
      from each other. The police encourage you to denounce your lover dooming them
      to a heavy penalty but helping you walk free.   You can\u2019t be sure if they
      will denounce you on their side dooming you in return. If both of you stay
      silent, the police will have to let you go for lack of evidence. Do you take
      this chance?  "
    answer1: "I denounce them to make sure I\u2019m safe"
    answer2: 'I stay loyal and take the risk of being betrayed '
  - question: 'You know a dark secret. Your childhood best friend committed a vicious
      murder. But someone else got convicted for it and is now on his way to the
      death penalty.   You have a choice, will you denounce your best friend knowing
      they will die for their crime or will you let the innocent man die to save
      your friend.  '
    answer1: I keep the secret and protect my friend
    answer2: 'I speak up and make sure the innocent man walks free '
  - question: 'Your mother is sick and has 3 months to live but only you know about
      her condition.   You can choose to hide it from her so that she can enjoy the
      last moments of her life as if everything is normal, or you can tell her so
      that she can make arrangements and say goodbye. '
    answer1: I hide the truth
    answer2: I tell her the truth
  - question: 'Your daughter and her best friend are swimming in the ocean when you
      realize they both got caught in a current. You get to them but notice that
      your daughter is stronger than her friend, struggling to keep afloat.   If
      you choose your daughter, her friend will definitely not make it.  If you save
      the friend first, chances are your daughter might not survive long enough for
      you to save her too.  '
    answer1: I save my daughter
    answer2: I bring the other child to safety first
  - question: 'You are now in charge of helping refugees get to shore  After a storm,
      the only option left is a small boat with a capacity of 7 people maximum but
      there are 30 refugees to save.   You can make sure 7 people get to shore, leaving
      the others to die at sea, knowing you will be judged and jailed for letting
      innocent people die.  Or you can take a chance and fill the boat with the 30
      refugees not knowing if you will reach the shore but sure that you will not
      end up in jail either way.  '
    answer1: I stay safe and secure 7 people
    answer2: 'I Fill the boat with everyone '
